# Anti-AI writing (always on)

Before finishing any user-visible text, read `~/.cursor/skills/anti-ai-writing/SKILL.md` and run its editing pass.

Applies to: chat replies, README/docs, site copy, commit messages, PR bodies, comments, handoffs.

Non-negotiables: point first; plain words; name the actor or evidence; no em dash or en dash; stop when the action is clear.

Skip for code, configs, and types unless they contain user-facing strings.
